        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hello,\n\nIt would be nice if depending on whether current page was requested via secured connection or unsecured, the helpers would return secured\/unsecured URLs appropriately.\nWhy this is important:\n\nSuppose I have a secured page https:\/\/domain.com\/test \nAll images\/asset files are served via HTTPS. However, the helpers output:\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"http:\/\/ajax.googleapis.com\/ajax\/libs\/jquery\/1.3.1\/jquery.min.js\"><\/script> \n<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"http:\/\/ajax.googleapis.com\/ajax\/libs\/jqueryui\/1.5.3\/jquery-ui.min.js\"><\/script> \n\nCausing some browsers to show security dialogs that not all content is secured. "
        },
